Node.Notes: Literally, "remembrance of his holiness," which probably refers to proclaiming God's holiness in worship. Some translate as "his holy name" on basis that remembrance and name are used in synonymous parallelism in ps135:13.
A verb like "comes" assumed (PP-S) or possibly "rejoicing belongs to the morning" (P-S).
Security or at rest and at ease.
Literally, "glory," which many change to "soul" on basis of parallelism in ps7:5 and 16:9.
